  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Communities at the Centre: Enabling FLER in Myanmar</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthen local organizations and CSOs capacity on emergency response at Ann, Mrauk U, Kyauk Taw, Buthidaung, Rathedaung. Support to FLER and establish Township-bus Coordination. Set up CFM, Develop and carried RNA , FLER plan and implement emergency response activities within 72 hours and 7 days.  Develop Township level protection referral mapping at targeted township</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This action has three components: 1) Local actors&#x2019; skills, capacities and knowledge are enhanced to lead responsibly managed, women-led FLER ; 2) Township contingency and response plans based on locally-led risk analysis established; and 3) FLER system designed and implemented of community- and women-led humanitarian mechanisms.</narrative>
  </description>
